@NODE GR_REG_Sections "Section/filebase list related gadgets"

 @{b}@{u}Description of gadgets:@{uu}@{ub}

 @{b}Parent@{ub}               - returns to section list if you are in
                        one of the section. Otherwise disabled.
                        As you see, @{b}Parent@{ub} button has no
                        shortcut, but you may use "Parent" function
                        from the @{b}Edit@{ub} menu, which do the same
                        as this button does for the current
                        source list, and should has own shortcut.

 @{b}Source/Destination@{ub}   - shows which list will be treated as source
                        while moving etc. You may change this by
                        clicking on the button @{b}Source/Dest...@{ub} under
                        the list you want to become source one.

 @{b}NOTE:@{ub} In most cases list becomes @{b}Source@{ub} list automatically when
       you click/doubleclick in it. In some cases it may be annoying
       e.g. if you move files from one upload section to all the rest
       and have to walk thru the destination tree to find the proper
       section for the file, but when you click the destination section
       it will become the source one... Can stand if you got 3 files
       to move, but if you got 100 or more... you have to use @{b}Un/Lock
       Source@{ub} menuitem from the @{b}Misc@{ub} menu to disable the automatic
       feature. But note you can still switch the source by clicking
       proper button without enabling the option.

@ENDNODE

@NODE GR_REG_Files "Files Imprt/Export gadgets"

 @{b}@{u}Description of gadgets:@{ub}@{uu}

 @{b}^@{ub}    - means the parent directory (if there's any)
 @{b}<@{ub}    - export files. If you want to copy out any file from 
        the BBS, just mark it, select the drawer you want
        it to be copied to and click this gadget.
 @{b}>@{ub}    - import files - the easiest way to add new files to the 
        database. Please read the @{b}Config/New@{ub}
 @{b}S/D@{ub}  - Source/Destination indicator/changer.

@ENDNODE

@NODE GR_Prawa "Section/filebase list related gadgets"

 @{b}@{u}Description of gadgets:@{uu}@{ub}

 @{b}Parent@{ub}               - returns to section list if you are in
                        one of the section. Otherwise disabled.
                        As you see, @{b}Parent@{ub} button has no
                        shortcut, but you may use "Parent" function
                        from the @{b}Edit@{ub} menu, which do the same
                        as this button does for the current
                        source list, and should has own shortcut.

 @{b}Source/Destination@{ub}   - shows which list will be treated as source
                        while moving etc. You may change this by
                        clicking on the button @{b}Source/Dest...@{ub} under
                        the list you want to become source one.

 @{b}NOTE:@{ub} In most cases list becomes @{b}Source@{ub} list automatically when
       you click/doubleclick in it. In some cases it may be annoying
       e.g. if you move files from one upload section to all the rest
       and have to walk thru the destination tree to find the proper
       section for the file, but when you click the destination section
       it will become the source one... Can stand if you got 3 files
       to move, but if you got 100 or more... you have to use @{b}Un/Lock
       Source@{ub} menuitem from the @{b}Misc@{ub} menu to disable the automatic
       feature. But note you can still switch the source by clicking
       proper button without enabling the option.

@ENDNODE

@NODE BT_All "All"

 @{b}@{u}All@{ub}@{uu}

 Selects all entries in Source listview

@ENDNODE

@NODE BT_EditEntry "Edit entry"

 @{b}@{u}Edit entry@{ub}@{uu}

 Allows you to edit selected entry (file or section).

@ENDNODE

@NODE BT_Move "Move"

 @{b}@{u}Move@{ub}@{uu}

 Moves marked files thru file sections (from Source to Destination)

@ENDNODE

@NODE BT_SetComment "Set file comment"

 @{b}@{u}Set file comment@{ub}@{uu}

 Allows you to change description of marked files

@ENDNODE

@NODE BT_Load "Load"

 @{b}@{u}Load BBS@{ub}@{uu}

 Load all BBS related files MaxManager needs to work properly

@ENDNODE

@NODE BT_None "Noone"

 @{b}@{u}None@{ub}@{uu}

 Deselects all selected items in Source listview

@ENDNODE

@NODE BT_Hunt "Hunt"

 @{b}@{u}Hunt@{ub}@{uu}

 Allows you to find file specified by (partial or whole) filename
 file comment etc. Supports wildcards as well.

@ENDNODE

@NODE BT_Rename "Rename"

 @{b}@{u}Rename@{ub}@{uu}

 Renames file in filebase @{b}and@{ub} if file exists on disk in 
 known path, also file on disk.

@ENDNODE

@NODE BT_PatternSelect "Pattern matching"

 @{b}@{u}Pattern matching@{ub}@{uu}

 Allows you to select files (in filebase or in import dir list!)
 matching given pattern. Matching file names or its comments is
 naturally possible.

@ENDNODE

@NODE BT_Save "Save BBS"

 @{b}@{u}Save BBS@{ub}@{uu}

 Save all databases the program work on. You must do this, otherwise
 all your work will be lost!

@ENDNODE

@NODE BT_Toggle "Toggle selection"

 @{b}@{u}Toggle selection@{ub}@{uu}

 Toggles state of entries in source listview: marked files become
 unmarked and vice-versa.

@ENDNODE

@NODE BT_Delete "Toggle delete"

 @{b}@{u}Toggle delete@{ub}@{uu}

 Marks file as @{b}deleted@{ub} or unmarks if it already was. Marking
 as deleted does @{b}NOT@{ub} means file is phisically removed! It 
 stays alive until you use @{b}Save@{ub} button (SAVE_BBS ARexx call)
 or flush deleted function. Then all files marked @{b}deleted@{ub} go
 in the past.

@ENDNODE

@NODE BT_Optimize "Optimize"

 @{b}@{u}Optimize@{ub}@{uu}

 MaxManager gives you various optimizers, using which lets you
 keep your BBS in order. Both global (acting on whole BBS) and
 section (working on selected section) optimizers are implemented
 as well as wide spectrum of functions in each of them.

@ENDNODE

@NODE BT_Quit "Quit"

 @{b}@{u}Quit@{ub}@{uu}

 Quits @{b}W.F.M.H. MaxManager@{ub}.

@ENDNODE

@NODE EditWindow "Edit Entry"

 @{b}@{u}Edit Window @{uu}@{ub}

 This window is used to edit files and related items (like desctription,
 flags, name of uploaded, download count and other things you should know
 from the MAX's itself. The one thing MAX's has not is the file disk
 scanner. To find the file on your disk (file must be online!) just
 click the "Find" button.

@ENDNODE

@NODE PrefsWindow "Preferences"

 @{b}@{u}Preferences window @{uu}@{ub}

 @{b}W.F.M.H. MaxManager@{ub} is designed to be not only powerful tool but to be
 flexible tool as well. Therefore you can set almost any thing which can
 be expected to be definable within the preferences window (which you
 may currently explore). As you probably guessed already, this window and
 its contents may be used to set the @{b}W.F.M.H. MaxManager@{ub} to apply your
 wishes. If you feel dizzy, just press HELP to find out meaning of the
 selected item.
@ENDNODE

@NODE ProgressWindow "Log window"

 @{b}@{u}Log window @{uu}@{ub}

 This is so-called log window. In @{b}W.F.M.H. MaxManager@{ub} it looks
 different in other programs, but it is used for the same task:
 to show what's up and how long is to finish. There's also "Abort"
 button to allow you to abort some (but not all) operations. Other
 buttons (@{b}Save@{ub} and @{b}Print@{ub}) allows you to store operation log after
 it become finished (it's very useful for optimalization and related
 functions, to see which files are processed and which are not and why).
 Log windows holds your whole sessions with @{b}MaxManager.@{ub} Reading the
 log you can find out which files you added, removed or changed etc.

 Those buttons are disabled for most of simplier operation.

 @{b}@{u}Meaning of available buttons: @{uu}@{ub}

 @{b}Abort@{ub} - forces currently performed operation to stop. If there are more
         tasks in queue (e.g. while optimalization), all of them will
         be canceled.

 @{b}Save@{ub}  - Allows you to save dump of contents of progress window as plain
         ASCII file. Useful if you want to analize e.g. results of
         performed operation later.

 @{b}Print@{ub} - Simmilar to @{b}Save@{ub} except it tries to redirect text to the
         printer instead of disk file.

@ENDNODE

@NODE RenameWindow "Rename"

 @{b}@{u}Rename Entry @{uu}@{ub}

 Renaming entries is easy. Just enter new name for the file or section
 (sections can be renamed in EditSection window too) and click @{b}Ok.@{ub} Note
 that file name have to be unique (program will check it automatically).
 Section name have not. If you are about to rename the file program
 will also try to rename corresponding file on the disk, and what
 more important, will scan whole pathes looking for potential victim!

 Right now this is rather simply feature and doesn't support wildcards
 or patterns.

 @{b}@{u}Explanation of gadgets: @{uu}@{ub}

 @{b}Ok@{ub}      - renames current file and getting the next from the queue if
           there's any
 @{b}Abort@{ub}   - cancels current file and returns to main window. All other
           files being in file queue will be skipped
 @{b}Cancel@{ub}  - cancels current file and getting the next from the queue
           if there's any.

@ENDNODE

@NODE SaveWindow "Save"

 @{b}@{u}Save the databases @{uu}@{ub}

@ENDNODE

@NODE FileHuntWindow "Hunt"

 @{b}@{u}Hunt for the file @{uu}@{ub}

 To help you find single file between thousands of various files
 stored in your filebase, @{b}W.F.M.H. MaxManager@{ub} gives you small
 but useful @{b}Hunt@{ub} function. The only thing you have to do is
 to enter name the searching file (function accepts AmigaDOS wilcards
 as well so you can look for many files matching given pattern), and
 to click @{b}Hunt@{ub} button. @{b}W.F.M.H. MaxManager@{ub} by default checks files'
 description so if you want it to use filenames only just use the
 @{b}Scan file comments as well@{ub} checkmark (checked - used). As you all
 know, if you use pattern "name", then files will have to match this
 pattern exectly (probably one file will be found, with name "name").
 To look for more files contains "name" somewhere in its file name
 you have to use "#?" at the begin and the end of pattern: "#?name#?".
 Because this may be annoying if you plan to Hunt more often than
 once a week, @{b}MaxManager@{ub} may bound the pattern automatically,
 corresponding to the state of the @{b}Round with #?@{ub} checkmark.
 @{b}Ignore deleted@{ub} will cause @{b}MaxManager@{ub} to ignore files marked
 as deleted while hunting.

 @{b}@{u}Using the wildcards: @{uu}@{ub}

 ?       Matches a single character.
 #       Matches the following expression 0 or more times.
 (ab|cd) Matches any one of the items seperated by '|'.
 ~       Negates the following expression.  It matches all strings
         that do not match the expression (aka ~(foo) matches all
         strings that are not exactly "foo").
 [abc]   Character class: matches any of the characters in the class.
 [~bc]   Character class: matches any of the characters not in the class.
 a-z     Character range (only within character classes). 
 %	      Matches 0 characters always (useful in "(foo|bar|%)").
 *       Synonym for "#?", not available by default in 2.0.  Available
         as an option that can be turned on.

 "Expression" in the above table means either a single character
 (ex: "#?"), or an alternation (ex: "#(ab|cd|ef)"), or a character
 class (ex: "#[a-zA-Z]").


 @{b}@{u}Hidden shortcuts: @{uu}@{ub}

 Press 'P' to activate pattern string.

@ENDNODE

@NODE EditSectionWindow "Edit Section"

 @{b}@{u}Edit section @{uu}@{ub}

 This window is similar to MAXsBBS's one, always used to edit
 section settings. I don't want to duplicate MAX's manual,
 so check it better out if you don't know available options.

 The only things I want to explain are buttons:

 @{b}Ok@{ub}      - applies changes and returns to main window
           (if you selected more sections with multiselect feature,
           then they will be skipped and won't be edited until
           you use "Edit" button again).
 @{b}Apply@{ub}   - applies changes and edit the next selected section
           (useful with multiselect)
 @{b}Cancel@{ub}  - closes the edit window without changing the *CURRENT*
           section settings. All section edited with multiselet,
           will remain unchanged!

 If you forgot to use multiselect and want to edit other section, just
 enter its number in dedicated string gadget and it appears ready to
 change. Do not forget to use @{b}Apply@{ub} before, as you changes made to
 previous edited section will be lost without warning.

@ENDNODE

@NODE STR_ES_SectionNumber "String Gadget"

 Edit section - Section number

 This field is mainly used to display number of section you actually
 edit. But you must know, that thare's also magic feature of this
 gadget. Enter any different (and valid!) section number to enter
 its settings without exiting-and-reentering this window.

 NOTE: All changes will be lost while changing section, so better
       use "Apply" gadget before.


 
@ENDNODE

@NODE OptimizeWindow "Global optimize"
@ENDNODE

@NODE StatisticsWindow "System statistics"

 @{b}@{u}Statistics @{uu}@{ub}

 This is feature has been made just for fun. It took me 5 minutes to design
 the window and 3 to code it. This is just statistics window, showing all
 most important information about your system like number of files (total
 and splitted to all four types) and number of users (total and splitted
 to six typical access levels).

 @{b}@{u}You can also click: @{uu}@{ub}

 @{b}Save@{ub}   - to save all those information as ASCII file or...
 @{b}Print@{ub}  - to print it on the paper and to show it to your frends later.
 @{b}Close@{ub}  - to exit to main window

@ENDNODE

@NODE SetComment "Set comment"

 @{b}@{u}Meaning of buttons:@{ub}@{uu}

 @{b}Ok   @{ub} - Accept comment of the file and takes next
 @{b}All  @{ub} - Set all marked files with this comment
 @{b}Skip @{ub} - Don't touch this file, let's see next one
 @{b}Abort@{ub} - Aborts whole operations

 @{b}@{u}Hidden hotkeys:@{ub}@{uu}

 Press 'C' to activate Comment string gadget
@ENDNODE

@NODE PatternWindow "Pattern matching"

 @{b}@{u}Selecting with pattern @{uu}@{ub}

 This allows you to select files and sections in the source list
 window based upon name (using AmigaDOS wildcards as well).
 For selection all standard wildcards are supported (#,~,? etc..):

 The patterns are fairly extensive, and approximate some of the ability
 of Unix/grep "regular expression" patterns.  Here are the available
 tokens:

 ?       Matches a single character.
 #       Matches the following expression 0 or more times.
 (ab|cd) Matches any one of the items seperated by '|'.
 ~       Negates the following expression.  It matches all strings
         that do not match the expression (aka ~(foo) matches all
         strings that are not exactly "foo").
 [abc]   Character class: matches any of the characters in the class.
 [~bc]   Character class: matches any of the characters not in the class.
 a-z     Character range (only within character classes). 
 %	      Matches 0 characters always (useful in "(foo|bar|%)").
 *       Synonym for "#?", not available by default in 2.0.  Available
         as an option that can be turned on.

 "Expression" in the above table means either a single character
 (ex: "#?"), or an alternation (ex: "#(ab|cd|ef)"), or a character
 class (ex: "#[a-zA-Z]").

 Using preferences module, you may predefine few mostly used patterns
 which will become available with one button click.

 This panel, as others, is fully controlable from the keys, but due
 to lack of labels it might not be so clear:

 @{b}@{u}Hidden shortcuts: @{uu}@{ub}

 P   - to activate pattern string gadget
 1-7 - to choose one of your predefined patterns

 Other shortcuts are visible so no docs is needed.

@ENDNODE

